<h4 id="Students">Students</h4>

<br/>
<b>Portability</b>
<p>Students should look for a laptop that is light-weight and portable so that it
may be taken from class to class with ease.  A laptop between 7 and 14 inches works best for most
students.  Netbooks are a popular option for many students because they are low-cost, have great portability, are 
light-weight, and they can last for many hours before the battery dies.  This was incredibly useful for me
while I was in college.  No doubt, the <a href="../laptops/acer">Acer Aspire</a> laptops are simply the best way to go
because they offer a great deal of features for such a low price.</p>
<br/>
<b>Features</b>
<p>The typical functions of a laptop fit for students include browsing the web, emailing, writing papers, and other basic operations,
all of which do not require a top-performance PC.  In that case, you won't need a super powerful PC as would a 
gamer (unless of course you want to use it for gaming also).  You should make sure it comes with Microsoft Office,
or if it doesn't, you can just buy it yourself.</p>
<br/>
<b>Price</b>
<p>Students should expect to pay little more than $500 for a laptop because most of them in this price range
    will fit the requirements above.
