<h4 id="Gamers">Gamers</h4>
<br/>

<b>Performance</b>
<p>Today's games require top-notch PC performance.  Serious gamers should look for cutting-edge processors, larger 
screen resolutions, advanced cooling systems, lots of RAM storage and preferably lots of hard drive space.  
The better the performance, the better your gaming experience will be.  Laptops such as <a href="../laptops/alienware">Alienware</a>
are ideal and very popular for gaming.  Be sure to get the latest processors, such as the Intel Core i7 or
Intel Core 2 Quad.  If you want to play games with high graphics, such as StarCraft 2, you will need an NVIDIA GeForce
graphics card or AMD Radeon HD at the least.  Also, high RAM is the least expensive way to improve your
PC performance so be sure to get at least 4 GB.</p> 
<br/>
<b>Maintenance</b>
<p>Since Gaming laptops are more costly, you won't be buying a new one too often.
    Instead, you're more likely to upgrade the parts that you already have, so be sure
    to pick one that is easy to upgrade.  You may also want to clean the fan with compressed air every month or so
in order to prevent dust buildup in the exhaust which causes your computer to get really hot and causes your computer
to crash when playing performance-demanding games.</p>
