<h4 id="Hobbyists">Hobbyists - Build Your Own PC</h4>
<br/>
<p>If you are an adventurer, you may consider building your own laptop.  This is a great
    alternative to buying from a computer manufacturer or reseller because you have complete
    control over everything that goes into your PC, and it will be easier to upgrade it with new parts in the
    future because you know exactly how your laptop is configured since you built it.  It also generally costs less
to build your own laptop, because you eliminate the entire profit margin of computer manufacturers that
you would otherwise have to pay.</p>
<br/>
<p>While this seems like a good idea, there is one downfall.  If your computer gets damaged, you 
    will not have tech support to guide you through the repair process, and also, there are no
    warranties on a computer you built on your own, so if your computer gets damaged, you will have to pay for all repairs regardless,
    and if it is totalled, say goodbye to it.</p>